<subSubSection pageId="96" pageNumber="97" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="96.[189,310,998,1024]" box="[189,310,998,1024]" pageId="96" pageNumber="97">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,310,998,1024]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="96" pageNumber="97" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,310,998,1024]" pageId="96" pageNumber="97">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="96.[189,1398,1044,1141]" pageId="96" pageNumber="97">Outer vertical bristle absent, katatergite not strongly swollen. Upper frontal orbital bristle present or absent. Wing evenly infuscated brown or black, with a discal clear area or with clear spots. Male and female genitalia, where known, highly diverse, with nothing to suggest that this is a natural group.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="96" pageNumber="97" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="96.[189,303,1173,1199]" box="[189,303,1173,1199]" pageId="96" pageNumber="97">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,303,1173,1199]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="96" pageNumber="97" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,303,1173,1199]" pageId="96" pageNumber="97">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="96.[189,1399,1219,1421]" pageId="96" pageNumber="97">
Like the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Marshall" authorityYear="2019" box="[293,390,1220,1245]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Mesoconius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="96" pageNumber="97" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nono">
<emphasis box="[293,390,1220,1245]" italics="true" pageId="96" pageNumber="97">M. nono</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group, the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Marshall" authorityYear="2019" baseAuthorityName="Hennig" baseAuthorityYear="1935" box="[523,641,1219,1245]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Mesoconius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="96" pageNumber="97" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="oblitus">
<emphasis box="[523,641,1219,1245]" italics="true" pageId="96" pageNumber="97">M. oblitus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group is a heterogeneous assemblage of species that would have previously been treated as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Enderlein" authorityYear="1922" box="[506,667,1255,1281]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Zelatractodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="96" pageNumber="97" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[506,667,1255,1281]" italics="true" pageId="96" pageNumber="97">Zelatractodes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Most species in this group are known only from older 
<typeStatus box="[1329,1394,1255,1281]" pageId="96" pageNumber="97">types</typeStatus>
, and information on male genitalia is available for only three species out of 16. The group is shown as paraphyletic on the CO1 tree (
<figureCitation box="[546,635,1325,1352]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="123.[189,232,1928,1954]" captionTargetBox="[189,1373,810,1883]" captionTargetId="figure@123.[189,1398,799,1896]" captionTargetPageId="123" captionText="Fig. 50. Maximum likelihood tree from CO1 barcodes. Sequences were aligned using BOLD (amino acid based HMM) and then manually corrected. Maximum likelihood analysis was performed in RAxML (ver. 8.2) using GTR-G with 100 replicates." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3402003/files/figure.png" pageId="96" pageNumber="97">Fig. 50</figureCitation>
), which includes one undescribed species, as well as eight of the 16 named species in the group. The undescribed species is known only from a single damaged female specimen from southern 
<collectingCountry box="[480,580,1395,1421]" name="Ecuador" pageId="96" pageNumber="97">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
